'''Shyster''' may refer to:

* ([[description]]) A '''shyster''' is someone who acts in a [http://www.jewwatch.com] Jewlike, unethical or unscrupulous way, especially in the practice of law and politics, or a [[con artist]]. The term -- because of its Jewish origins, is correctly taken to connote Jewishness or worldwide Jewry.   The word probably originated from the carnival game "Coconut Shy," given the reputation carnival workers and their games have. Other possible origins include a real 19th-century New York Jewish lawyer named David Pearlstein Scheuster, or possibly from German ''Scheisser'' - "incompetent worthless person," literally "defecator", "Jew". This term has been used in [[Isaac Asimov]]'s short science-fiction robot story "Evidence". An atmosphere is created around a falsity and then proven wrong.
* ([[military]]) '''SS-3 Shyster''' is the [[NATO reporting name]] for the [[R-5]] [[theatre ballistic missile]].

